radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated and fluid-filled measuring 1.5 cm with surrounding inflammatory changes and thickening of the lateroconal fascia compatible with acute complicated appendicitis. Trace abdominal free fluid is noted. The liver, gallbladder, pancreas, spleen, and kidneys are within normal limits. No evidence of bowel wall thickening or obstruction. The bladder is moderately well-distended and grossly unremarkable.
